text: Arizona's 9th Legislative District is one of 30 in the state, located entirely in Pima County. As of 2018 there are 57 precincts in the district, with a total registered voter population of 120,091. ==Political representation== The district is represented for the 2019-2021 Legislative Session in the State Senate by Victoria Steele (D, Tucson) and in the House of Representatives by Pamela Hannley (D, Tucson) and Randall Friese (D, Tucson). ==References== Category:Pima County, Arizona Category:Arizona legislative districts
title: Arizona's 9th legislative district
